other_tests.findings: Histamine-releasing autoantibodies detected in patient serum.
Positive for house dust mite and birch; negative for formoterol, salmeterol, bambuterol, ipratropium, and methylprednisolone.
Symptomatic decrease in FEV1 from 3.15 to 1.94 L (38% drop) after inhalation of terbutaline dry powder.
other_tests.changes_over_time: At 3-year follow-up, asthma is controlled with specific medications.
